The number of Covid-19 deaths in SA climbed past 150, with the health ministry confirming five additional fatalities on Wednesday. In a statement, health minister Dr Zweli Mkhize said that the death toll now stood at 152 following two additional deaths in both the Western Cape and KwaZulu-Natal, and one death in Limpopo. There were 7,808 confirmed cases countrywide, Mkhize said, an increase of 236 from Tuesday. The Western Cape remained the country's Covid-19 epicentre, both in terms of deaths and number of cases. The number of recoveries was 3,153 - with the Western Cape and Gauteng both passing 1,000 recoveries. The provincial breakdown of cases on Wednesday was provided as: The number of deaths and recoveries were recorded as: